text.section:
The Cabinet for Economic Development shall take all of the following factors into consideration when determining which applicants shall receive financial assistance under this section:
The benefit of the remedy to human health, safety, and the environment;
The permanence of the remedy;
The cost-effectiveness of the remedy in comparison with other alternatives;
The financial condition of the applicant;
The financial or economic distress of the area in which the cleanup is being conducted; and
The potential for economic development.
